===Other writing===
In the popular press, Davis' work appeared in "[[Scientific American]]," "Science," the "[[New York Times Magazine]]," "[[Commentary (magazine)|Commentary]]," "[[Foreign Affairs]]" and numerous newspapers.<ref>[http://www.stanford.edu/dept/news/pr/97/970305davisobit.html Obituary] at Stanford News</ref>

In 1957, Davis predicted that population of the world would reach six billion by the year 2000. He was remarkably close; that population figure was reached in October 1999.<ref>[http://www.bookrags.com/biography/kingsley-davis-soc Bookrags.com]</ref>

